Introduction

Factors are used to work with categorical variables

Cc function s dng trong trong chapter

sort(): sp xp d liu trong array.
factor(): gn levels cho variables.
parse_factor(): gn levels cho factors nhng c bo warning.
fct_reorder(): sp xp factor li theo mt bin khc.
fct_relevel(): a li level ban u + u tin level no.
fct_reorder2(): sp xp factor li theo 2 bin khc.
fct_recode(): i tn level ca factor li.
fct_rev(): o ngc li.
fct_infreq(): i factor theo tun sut xut hin tng dn.
fct_collapse(): nhp nhiu level thnh 1 level.
fct_lump_n(): gi level c tun sut cao nht, v gp cc level cn li thnh mt.
fct_collapse(): ghp cc level li thnh mt level.
fct_infreq(): sp xp theo tn sut xut hin level.

Factor level khng phi l bin ordinal m ch sp xp th t xut hin v quy nh cc gi tr mc nh. # Pratice

a string is sorted by alphabet

x1 <- c("Dec","Apr","Jan","Mar")
sort(x1)
## [1] "Apr" "Dec" "Jan" "Mar"

a string is sorted by month

month_levels <- c("Jan","Feb","Mar","Apr","May","Jun","Jul","Aug","Sep","Oct","Nov","Dec")

y1<- factor(x1, levels=month_levels)
y1
## [1] Dec Apr Jan Mar
## Levels: Jan Feb Mar Apr May Jun Jul Aug Sep Oct Nov Dec
sort(y1)
## [1] Jan Mar Apr Dec
## Levels: Jan Feb Mar Apr May Jun Jul Aug Sep Oct Nov Dec
x2 <- c("Apr","Jam","aug","Nov")
sort(x2)
## [1] "Apr" "aug" "Jam" "Nov"
y2 <- factor(x2,levels=month_levels)
y2
## [1] Apr  <NA> <NA> Nov 
## Levels: Jan Feb Mar Apr May Jun Jul Aug Sep Oct Nov Dec

alphabetical order in a factor

factor(x1)
## [1] Dec Apr Jan Mar
## Levels: Apr Dec Jan Mar

keep the order of the first appearance in the data

factor(x1, levels= unique(x1))
## [1] Dec Apr Jan Mar
## Levels: Dec Apr Jan Mar

or

f2 <- x1 %>% factor() %>% fct_inorder()
f2
## [1] Dec Apr Jan Mar
## Levels: Dec Apr Jan Mar

access the set of valid levels directly

levels(f2)
## [1] "Dec" "Apr" "Jan" "Mar"

f <- factor(c("a", "b", "c", "d"), levels = c("b", "c", "d", "a"))
f
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: b c d a
fct_relevel(f)
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: b c d a
fct_relevel(f, "a")
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: a b c d
fct_relevel(f, "b", "a")
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: b a c d

Move to the third position

fct_relevel(f, "a", after = 2)
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: b c a d

Relevel to the end

fct_relevel(f, "a", after = Inf)
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: b c d a
fct_relevel(f, sort)
## [1] a b c d
## Levels: a b c d

changer lordre de levels

x = c("van","thu","vi")
x= factor(x)

levels(x) <- c("vi","van","thu")
levels(x)
## [1] "vi"  "van" "thu"

pardfaut, fct_reorder2() utilise function last2 (trier les valeurs de prop la dernire groupe dge(89 ans) first2: trier les valeurs de prop la premire groupe dge(18 ans) labs() = labels

by_age <- gss_cat %>%
  filter(!is.na(age)) %>%
  count(age, marital) %>%
  group_by(age) %>%
  mutate(prop = n / sum(n))

ggplot(by_age, aes(age, prop, colour = marital)) +
  geom_line(na.rm = TRUE)

ggplot(by_age, aes(age, prop, colour = fct_reorder2(marital, age, prop))) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(colour = "marital")

ggplot(by_age, aes(age, prop, colour = fct_reorder2(marital, age, prop,.fun = first2))) +
  geom_line() +
  labs(colour = "marital")

fct_rev() renverse order of factor levels fct_infreq() reorder factor levels by frequency

gss_cat %>% count(marital)
## # A tibble: 6  2
##   marital           n
##   <fct>         <int>
## 1 No answer        17
## 2 Never married  5416
## 3 Separated       743
## 4 Divorced       3383
## 5 Widowed        1807
## 6 Married       10117
gss_cat %>% ggplot(aes(marital))+
  geom_bar()

gss_cat %>%
  mutate(marital = marital %>% fct_infreq() %>% fct_rev()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(marital)) +
    geom_bar()

gss_cat %>%
  mutate(marital = marital %>% fct_infreq()) %>%
  ggplot(aes(marital)) +
    geom_bar()
